# unicode_palette

Unicode is now almost ubiquitous, and it has a very rich set of symbols and emojis that one can use to visually improve their communication.

The question is how to find and use them.

Easy: here is a [palette](data:text/plain;charset=UTF-8;base64,) of all Unicode symbols (as of Python 3.11) as a data: URL.
You can just bookmark it and always have this visual palette handy.
